    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Jerusalem's Significance Predates Birth of Jesus</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Hyman Adelman letter on Medhat Credi's October 15 letter notes there were no Christians living in Jerusalem before or during life of Jesus Christ, who was a Jew (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In response to Medhat Credi's letter [''Jerusalem's Meaning for People Besides Jews,'' Oct. 15], I would like to point out that there were no Christians living in Jerusalem before, or during the life of Jesus Christ. Jesus was born, bred and died a Jew. In fact, he was hailed as king of the Jews, not Christians.</p>
        <p>HYMAN ADELMAN  Somers</p>
      </block>
